A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a craftsman's workbench viewed from above, featuring architectural blueprints with geometric grid patterns, a compass, wooden drafting tools, and translucent overlapping sheets showing abstract flowchart-like diagrams. The color palette uses warm sepia tones, muted teals, and cream whites with subtle paper texture throughout. Small mechanical gears and interconnected nodes float above the workspace, suggesting the transformation of traditional design into systematic digital structure. The composition has the aesthetic of mid-century technical manuals with clean lines and deliberate negative space.
